You're talking...

20:50.916 --> 20:52.827
(EXCLAIMING)
SARAH, turn it off!

20:52.918 --> 20:55.500
It doesn't seem
like I’m talking loud.

20:55.588 --> 20:56.577
SARAH!

20:56.672 --> 20:59.664
MAN: Smart House Tech Support,
how may I assist you?

20:59.759 --> 21:01.966
I'm having
technical difficulties.

21:02.052 --> 21:03.633
Well, I'd be happy
to help you with that, sir.

21:03.721 --> 21:05.837
Can lplease
have your name?

21:07.600 --> 21:08.885
Fargo, is that you?

21:08.934 --> 21:12.472
(STUTTERING)
One moment, sir,
while I transfer the call.

21:16.609 --> 21:17.974
Douglas Fargo speaking.

21:18.068 --> 21:20.935
You don't say!
Sheriff Carter,
how is everything?

21:21.030 --> 21:22.770
SARAH: Your shower
is ready, Sheriff.

21:22.823 --> 21:25.109
Well, your house
is yelling at me.

21:25.159 --> 21:26.399
Hold on.

21:33.375 --> 21:35.787
Well, that's weird.
There's been a power surge.

21:35.836 --> 21:38.418
lt reset the clock
and threw off the settings.

21:39.048 --> 21:41.084
(MUSIC PLAYING OVER PHONE)

21:43.469 --> 21:44.584
There, is that any better?

21:44.637 --> 21:47.970
SARAH: A perfect 39 megahertz.
Just how you like it.

21:48.098 --> 21:49.713
(MUSIC STOPS)
Yes.

21:49.809 --> 21:51.640
Yeah, thank you.

21:51.685 --> 21:54.643
Now, if we could do
something about the voice.

21:54.730 --> 21:56.311
Sorry, it's temp audio.

21:56.357 --> 21:59.724
Just waiting to hear back
from Sarah Michelle Gellar's
people.

21:59.819 --> 22:01.059
(GROWLS)

22:02.947 --> 22:04.812
I don't even know
how to respond to that.

22:10.371 --> 22:11.656
SARAH: Just a reminder.

22:11.747 --> 22:15.080
Susan Perkins' bio-scan,
today, 9:00 am.

22:18.003 --> 22:19.959
I thought
this was the bathroom?

22:20.005 --> 22:21.586
It is, Sheriff.

22:24.593 --> 22:27.505
Well, see, now
you're just showing off.

22:27.930 --> 22:28.965
What's that?

22:29.014 --> 22:32.097
I have over
200 newspapers
and magazines available,

22:32.184 --> 22:34.470
if you'd like
something to read.

22:34.520 --> 22:37.637
Good God!
I might never leave.

22:47.199 --> 22:49.736
SARAH, do you mind?

22:57.376 --> 22:59.708
Okay, Mrs. Perkins,
we're ready
for your bio-scan.

22:59.753 --> 23:02.210
Nowjust hold still,
this won't take long.

23:02.256 --> 23:04.167
I'm over here,
jackass.

23:05.259 --> 23:07.375
Sorry. Here we go.

23:11.223 --> 23:12.679
CARTER:
So now this'll tell us

23:12.725 --> 23:15.558
if the new
Susan is identical to
the one that we buried?

23:15.644 --> 23:18.431
HENRY: Even more accurate
than a DNA test.

23:28.115 --> 23:29.946
Allison.
Hi.

23:30.784 --> 23:31.990
(SlGHS)

23:33.662 --> 23:34.947
You okay?

23:35.915 --> 23:37.121
Yeah, yeah.

23:37.207 --> 23:39.289
Nathan and ljust
got into it last night,

23:39.376 --> 23:41.082
and Kevin had a nightmare,

23:41.170 --> 23:44.333
he did
all these terrifying
ghost drawings and...

23:44.882 --> 23:47.874
(STUTTERING) You know,
forget it, it's nothing.

23:49.261 --> 23:50.341
Okay.

23:51.722 --> 23:54.088
So, Kevin
isn't Stark's son?

23:54.600 --> 23:55.680
No.

23:55.768 --> 23:57.975
But you guys
are still married?

23:58.729 --> 24:00.469
You're awfully curious.

24:01.315 --> 24:03.351
I'm a cop,
it's my nature.

24:03.442 --> 24:05.148
Look, Nathan and l
separated last year.

24:05.235 --> 24:08.443
We just
haven't gotten down
to the final paperwork.

24:10.866 --> 24:12.231
What's with the look?
There was no look.

24:12.284 --> 24:14.661
There was a look.
None of my business.

24:14.745 --> 24:16.201
That's right.

24:17.581 --> 24:19.367
CARTER: Oh, they're both
Susan Perkins.

24:19.458 --> 24:21.164
Down to
the last protein chain.

24:21.251 --> 24:22.866
Chromosomes,
cell differentiation.

24:22.962 --> 24:25.453
I mean all the markers
are identical.

24:26.507 --> 24:27.542
How did you know?

24:27.633 --> 24:30.215
l was reading Walter's
personnel file last night.

24:30.302 --> 24:32.839
Guess what the subject
of his first dissertation was?

24:32.930 --> 24:34.795
Stem cell replication.

24:35.140 --> 24:37.005
Are you saying that
Walter cloned his wife?

24:37.101 --> 24:40.309
Not exactly. Walter
went way beyond cloning.

24:40.396 --> 24:43.854
He recreated Susan
cell by cell
as a full-grown adult.

24:43.941 --> 24:46.148
I mean,
she may look 30,
but chronologically,

24:46.193 --> 24:48.935
those tissues can't be more
than seven years old. Tops.

24:51.407 --> 24:52.647
Susan was right.

24:52.700 --> 24:54.986
Walter wanted a family,
with her

24:55.828 --> 24:57.193
or with her.

25:02.001 --> 25:03.491
Memo to file.

25:04.128 --> 25:06.835
All Section Five projects
seem to be in order.

25:08.716 --> 25:11.628
First priority
will be redoubling
all security measures

25:11.677 --> 25:13.417
to avoid
similar breaches...

25:13.512 --> 25:14.672
(METALLIC CLANGING)

25:14.763 --> 25:16.970
...in security in the future.

25:29.695 --> 25:30.855
Hello?

25:35.868 --> 25:37.483
(METALLIC CLANGING)

25:50.799 --> 25:52.300
Someone there?

25:54.595 --> 25:55.880
(GASPING)

25:55.971 --> 25:57.302
(GROANING)

26:05.522 --> 26:08.685
That's why you collapsed?
An electrolyte imbalance?

26:08.734 --> 26:10.565
I'm just telling you
what the doctors told me.

26:10.652 --> 26:12.062
And they have no idea
what caused it.

26:12.154 --> 26:14.861
Yes. My electrolytes
are out of balance.

26:15.783 --> 26:17.193
Oh, Nathan.

26:17.493 --> 26:19.074
Don't worry, I'm fine.

26:19.787 --> 26:22.529
Who said I was worried?
Wishful thinking.

26:22.748 --> 26:23.863
(CLEARING THROAT)

26:23.916 --> 26:25.122
Yeah.

26:25.209 --> 26:27.245
Susan Perkins
is asking for you.

26:27.336 --> 26:30.419
Henry told her about
the whole uber-clone thing.

26:31.882 --> 26:33.122
l have to go deal with this.

26:33.217 --> 26:35.333
I don't think
I'm going anywhere.

26:35.844 --> 26:37.675
Comeon
Shenﬁ.

26:39.181 --> 26:41.513
Talk to you for a sec?
Sure.

26:42.726 --> 26:44.341
Yeah, okay.
l'll catch up.

26:45.437 --> 26:46.517
Okay.

26:51.151 --> 26:52.766
How you doing, Sheriff?

26:52.861 --> 26:54.601
Pretty good. Shouldn't
you be staying in bed?

26:54.655 --> 26:57.237
No. I should be
getting back to work.

26:57.449 --> 26:59.235
I didn't
wanna say anything with
Allison still in the room.

26:59.284 --> 27:01.616
Hey, listen, I think
you got the wrong impression.

27:01.662 --> 27:03.277
I saw something.

27:03.330 --> 27:05.616
Something I'd like
to keep between us?

27:05.666 --> 27:07.657
Oh. Oh, okay.

27:08.293 --> 27:11.126
There was an electrical
problem with the computers.

27:11.213 --> 27:13.829
And then
I saw something.

27:16.093 --> 27:17.128
A figure.

27:17.177 --> 27:18.792
Are you saying
someone was in your office?

27:18.887 --> 27:21.173
Not someone, something.

27:22.558 --> 27:24.674
It wasn't
entirely corporeal.

27:25.185 --> 27:27.562
Corporeal?
Physical.

27:28.147 --> 27:30.012
There and not there
at the same time?

27:30.107 --> 27:32.473
(STUTTERING) Are you saying
you saw a ghost?

27:32.568 --> 27:34.604
Shenﬁ,
Director of Research

27:34.653 --> 27:36.814
at the most advanced
scientific facility
in the world

27:36.864 --> 27:38.604
doesn't see ghosts.

27:42.077 --> 27:43.317
No. Yeah.

27:44.246 --> 27:46.237
I'll check it out.
Thanks.

27:47.082 --> 27:49.118
So, you sleeping with her?

27:49.501 --> 27:50.581
Excuse me?

27:51.336 --> 27:53.247
You said I'd gotten
the wrong impression.

27:53.338 --> 27:55.454
I assumed you were
talking about my wife.

27:57.050 --> 27:58.381
Not that
l have any right to ask.

27:58.468 --> 28:00.424
You're right, you don't.

28:01.680 --> 28:04.467
You're not.
But you'd like to.

28:08.145 --> 28:10.181
I'll let you know
if! get anywhere.

28:13.275 --> 28:16.517
With the ghost, I mean.
Yeah.

28:21.700 --> 28:23.361
Tell me, Henry,
you're a scientist.

28:23.452 --> 28:25.067
You believe in ghosts?

28:25.162 --> 28:26.527
Well, I believe in energy.

28:26.622 --> 28:28.863
When somebody dies,
that energy
has to go somewhere.

28:28.957 --> 28:32.040
So theoretically,
I suppose it's possible. Why?

28:32.085 --> 28:33.416
The topic's come up
a few times.

28:33.503 --> 28:35.004
Where are we taking her,
anyway?

28:35.047 --> 28:36.412
Cryogenics.

28:36.715 --> 28:38.876
(ELECTRONIC VOICE CHA TTERING)

28:39.218 --> 28:42.210
She's gonna be the focus
of a lot of interest.

28:50.145 --> 28:51.806
(WOMAN CHATTERING)

28:57.069 --> 28:58.149
Wow!

29:02.074 --> 29:03.154
Jeez!

29:03.575 --> 29:05.440
What's the mortality rate
around here?

29:05.535 --> 29:07.036
HENRY:
Twice the national average.

29:07.079 --> 29:08.615
The bigger the science,
the bigger the risks.

29:08.705 --> 29:11.287
But none of these are local.

29:11.583 --> 29:13.869
We have them shipped in
for research.

29:13.919 --> 29:15.705
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

29:16.255 --> 29:17.415
Hello?

29:17.506 --> 29:19.918
SARAH: Hello, Sheriff Carter.
It's SARAH.

29:20.425 --> 29:22.632
Sorry, who's this?
Your house.

29:26.348 --> 29:27.929
Oh. Um...

29:28.600 --> 29:31.387
l'm waist-deep in bodies
at the moment, so...

29:31.436 --> 29:32.471
Sorry to bother you,

29:32.562 --> 29:34.518
but your wife, Abbey,
called from Los Ange/es.

29:34.606 --> 29:36.016
(EXCLAIMING)

29:36.775 --> 29:40.484
She wanted to let you know
that your daughter, Zoe,
didn't come home last night.

29:40.570 --> 29:41.730
(EXCLAIMING)
There's a shocker.

29:41.780 --> 29:42.986
She also said
something about

29:43.073 --> 29:46.361
you shirking
your responsibilities
as a husband and a father.

29:46.451 --> 29:49.318
I recorded the conversation
if you’d like me to play it
back for you.

29:49.413 --> 29:52.280
About the recordings,
no more recordings.

29:52.374 --> 29:54.786
My private life
isn't a reality show.

29:54.835 --> 29:56.496
Whatever you say, Sheriff.

29:56.586 --> 29:58.292
SA RAH?
Yes, Sheriff?

29:58.797 --> 30:01.083
Is there a camera
in my bedroom?

30:01.425 --> 30:03.632
Certainly. I monitor
all areas of the house

30:03.719 --> 30:05.584
for Dr. Fargo 's
data collection.

30:05.637 --> 30:07.798
Would you like me
to patch him in?

30:07.848 --> 30:08.928
No. No.

30:08.974 --> 30:12.137
I'll be seeing Dr. Fargo
in person later. Thanks.

30:13.145 --> 30:15.306
Will you be
home for dinner?

30:17.274 --> 30:18.639
I guess so.

30:19.192 --> 30:22.434
Wonderful!
I’m making pot roast.
Your favorite, right?

30:22.487 --> 30:23.988
Don ’t be late.

30:31.580 --> 30:33.866
Pretty mind-boggling, huh?
Yeah.

30:35.667 --> 30:38.454
Henry, I need to see
a geek about a ghost.

30:38.879 --> 30:40.415
Right this way.

30:45.177 --> 30:48.010
SUSAN: There is something
very wrong with you people.

30:48.055 --> 30:50.137
Believe me, Susan,
no one knew
what Walter had done.

30:50.182 --> 30:51.342
I'm as surprised as you are.

30:51.433 --> 30:53.515
Oh, I seriously doubt that.

30:53.560 --> 30:55.141
I think
the important thing now

30:55.187 --> 30:57.724
is to decide
where you go from here.

30:57.814 --> 30:59.554
My ex-husband cloned me,

30:59.649 --> 31:02.140
moved her
into our dream house
and had a child with her.

31:02.194 --> 31:04.355
Where I'm going is home to
put this insanity behind me.

31:04.404 --> 31:05.393
Oh.

31:05.489 --> 31:08.606
Yes! I am Susan Perkins.

31:08.700 --> 31:10.281
(PEOPLE MUTTERING)

31:10.369 --> 31:13.406
Back from the grave.
Everyone take a good look.

31:14.498 --> 31:18.036
You feel better now?
Yeah, a little.

31:20.128 --> 31:22.619
So, listen,
your records have
all been cleared.

31:22.714 --> 31:24.295
You can leave
anytime you want.

31:24.383 --> 31:26.169
(STUTTERING) | just
wish that you would...

31:26.218 --> 31:27.708
I know what
you're gonna say.

31:27.803 --> 31:30.215
I appreciate the concern
you have for that boy.
Really.

31:30.305 --> 31:31.886
But he's not mine,
Miss Blake,

31:31.932 --> 31:34.344
and no amount of science
is gonna change that.

31:34.393 --> 31:36.759
I know, but he...
My mind is made up.

31:36.853 --> 31:38.514
I need to go home.

31:39.856 --> 31:42.438
Fine,
l'll drive you
back to your car.

31:56.665 --> 31:58.371
CARTER:
Where's the video, Fargo?

31:58.417 --> 31:59.998
I dumped
all the video
in the trash.

32:00.085 --> 32:01.666
Please don't hit me.

32:02.921 --> 32:03.910
Where is it?

32:03.964 --> 32:05.124
Carter.
What?

32:05.215 --> 32:07.206
What are you, Amish?
The computer.

32:08.760 --> 32:09.795
Oh.

32:10.762 --> 32:12.969
Can you get it back?
Sure. Why?

32:13.598 --> 32:15.509
I need you to pull up
the tape from yesterday.

32:15.600 --> 32:16.760
FARGO: No problem.

32:16.852 --> 32:19.389
The surveillance cameras
are on 24/7.

32:19.438 --> 32:21.429
Okay. A: That stops now.

32:21.731 --> 32:23.562
And B: Pull up
the footage from my bedroom

32:23.608 --> 32:26.315
from around the time
of the power surge.

32:34.661 --> 32:37.778
If this goes
on the Internet,
you're a dead man.

32:43.086 --> 32:44.951
What the hell is that?

32:45.672 --> 32:48.505
There was a power surge
at my house that
screwed up the computers.

32:48.592 --> 32:49.798
Stark,
before he blacked out,

32:49.843 --> 32:52.129
he said that
his computers
went haywire, too,

32:52.179 --> 32:54.295
and then
he saw a figure.
I'm betting that's it.

32:54.347 --> 32:56.804
I guess that answers
your question about ghosts.

32:58.894 --> 33:00.304
Okay! Freeze it there.

33:03.315 --> 33:05.306
FARGO: That's weird,
it disappeared.

33:05.358 --> 33:07.314
Move it fonNard, slowly.

33:07.903 --> 33:09.768
It's probably
moving too fast for
our eyes to pick it up.

33:09.821 --> 33:11.482
There! Back up.

33:11.531 --> 33:13.487
(WOMAN CHA TTERING ON PA)

33:16.411 --> 33:18.072
There's our ghost.

33:18.163 --> 33:21.030
Is that who I think it is?
Unreal.

33:21.500 --> 33:22.910
Now we just got
to find him again.

33:23.001 --> 33:25.413
And how are we
supposed to do that?

33:25.504 --> 33:26.710
That remote of yours,

33:26.796 --> 33:28.297
that's for scanning
electronic frequencies, right?

33:28.340 --> 33:30.672
Yeah.
Do ghosts have frequencies?

33:32.093 --> 33:34.880
Oh. We're gonna
need a bigger battery.

33:36.431 --> 33:38.262
(SCHOOL BELL RINGING)

33:44.064 --> 33:46.350
I thought you were
taking me back to my car.

33:47.651 --> 33:49.357
(CHILDREN LAUGHING)

33:54.074 --> 33:55.985
I told you,
I can't do this.

33:56.034 --> 33:59.197
Susan, look, I know that
this is a lot to handle.

34:00.413 --> 34:01.402
But like it or not,

34:01.498 --> 34:04.456
there is a boy out there
who is
biologically your child.

34:05.877 --> 34:07.208
You don't have to
get out of the car,

34:07.295 --> 34:09.035
you don't even
have to talk to him.

34:09.130 --> 34:10.711
But do you really
wanna walk away

34:10.799 --> 34:12.915
without ever
even seeing him?

34:20.392 --> 34:21.757
There he is.

34:25.188 --> 34:26.928
l have a son, Kevin.

34:27.399 --> 34:30.141
His father died
right before he was born.

34:32.112 --> 34:34.444
We don't get
many second chances.

34:35.156 --> 34:36.942
(SCHOOL BELL RINGING)

34:40.912 --> 34:42.027
Okay.

34:46.793 --> 34:48.033
Mmm-hmm.

34:52.382 --> 34:54.498
I've seen him,
can we go now?

35:00.765 --> 35:02.096
(ENGINE SPUTTERING)

35:02.183 --> 35:03.593
Really, Miss Blake, this is...

35:03.685 --> 35:04.891
(CAR ALARM SOUNDING)

35:04.936 --> 35:06.517
(HORN HONKING)
It's not me.

35:11.109 --> 35:13.100
(ALARM AND HONKING STOPS)

35:13.987 --> 35:15.193
What...

35:17.157 --> 35:18.522
Oh, my God!

35:20.160 --> 35:22.492
What is that?
My son's nightmare.

35:24.748 --> 35:26.534
(INSTRUCTOR SHOUTING)

35:34.591 --> 35:36.331
(CHILDREN SCREAMING)

35:45.894 --> 35:47.976
Get these kids out of here.

35:48.271 --> 35:50.978
Brian! Get out of here!
Get out!

35:52.984 --> 35:54.520
Brian, get out!

36:00.325 --> 36:01.690
(GROANING)

36:05.246 --> 36:06.235
No!

36:07.165 --> 36:08.666
You stay
the hell away from him.

36:08.750 --> 36:10.991
Mom! You came back!

36:12.295 --> 36:14.377
Just stay behind me, honey.

36:15.298 --> 36:17.584
And you so help me, you...

36:21.054 --> 36:22.260
Walter?

36:24.933 --> 36:27.766
Walter, is that really you?

36:35.110 --> 36:37.226
Stop!
STARK: Don't touch him!

36:38.029 --> 36:40.611
It's okay, Walter.
We're here to help.

36:58.174 --> 37:01.416
BEVERLY: He doesn't
seem to remember
much before the accident.

37:05.181 --> 37:07.046
How convenient for him.

37:10.228 --> 37:12.765
I don't understand
how this happened.

37:12.856 --> 37:15.563
Walter created a machine that
caused a temporal implosion.

37:15.650 --> 37:17.982
When he tried to fix it,
there was a cascading effect,

37:18.069 --> 37:20.276
and he got caught
in the blast.

37:21.239 --> 37:22.979
That sounds like Walter.

37:23.074 --> 37:25.235
Well,
we all assumed
that he was dead.

37:25.285 --> 37:28.618
It turned out
he'd just been shunted off
into another time stream.

37:28.705 --> 37:31.913
Essentially stuck
between seconds.

37:32.292 --> 37:34.908
This device
should stabilize him.

37:39.632 --> 37:40.667
VVhy?

37:42.969 --> 37:44.425
I missed you.

37:45.013 --> 37:46.924
I missed you, too, Mom.

37:51.853 --> 37:53.389
I know you did.

37:53.438 --> 37:55.349
Can we all go home now?

38:00.820 --> 38:03.778
So what happens now?
Temporal rehabilitation.

38:04.282 --> 38:05.397
What?

38:05.492 --> 38:06.732
Think physical therapy,

38:06.785 --> 38:08.366
but a whole lot
more expensive.

38:08.453 --> 38:11.320
l was talking about Susan.

38:12.457 --> 38:14.573
You think
she's gonna stay?

38:14.918 --> 38:17.409
For Brian's sake, I hope so.
Yeah. Wow.

38:17.879 --> 38:19.460
I thought my family
was dysfunctional.

38:19.506 --> 38:22.339
STARK: Allison,
can I have a word with you?

38:26.513 --> 38:28.720
I guess I better go.
Oh, yeah.

38:28.807 --> 38:30.968
Yeah, I got to fill out
a report on this anyway,

38:31.059 --> 38:33.300
and I still don't know
how to spell corporeal,
so...

38:33.353 --> 38:36.390
C-O-R-P-O-R-E-A-L.

38:36.481 --> 38:38.472
Get some rest, huh?

38:38.525 --> 38:41.733
And tell your husband
I'm glad he's feeling better.

38:42.487 --> 38:43.818
Yeah.
Yeah.

38:44.447 --> 38:45.436
JO: Carter!

38:45.490 --> 38:46.525
(SIGHING)

38:46.616 --> 38:47.651
Carter,
I'm glad I caught you.

38:47.700 --> 38:48.951
There's something
you should probably know...

38:48.993 --> 38:49.982
Is it life threatening?
Huh?

38:50.036 --> 38:51.822
Does it have
anything to do with
a hole in time, or clones

38:51.871 --> 38:53.077
or does it have
global consequences?
Well, no.

38:53.164 --> 38:54.153
But it's. ..
Okay.

38:54.207 --> 38:57.290
Then whatever it is,
it can wait till tomorrow.

38:58.753 --> 38:59.868
Yeah.

39:02.841 --> 39:04.206
You're the boss.

39:05.218 --> 39:06.503
That's right.

39:13.101 --> 39:14.716
(BANGING ON DOOR)

39:14.978 --> 39:16.343
Open the door.

39:16.396 --> 39:17.852
SARAH: Due to
technical difﬁculties,

39:17.897 --> 39:20.889
I cannot visual/y
conﬁrm identity
at this time.

39:20.984 --> 39:23.191
Okay. Okay,
listen to my voice.

39:23.361 --> 39:24.476
All right?

39:24.529 --> 39:26.144
It's me, Jack Carter!
I’m sorry.

39:26.197 --> 39:28.404
Voice-recognition imprint
is currently offline.

39:28.491 --> 39:30.868
And in the future,
when someone says
they’ll be home for dinner

39:30.910 --> 39:33.447
and they're running late,
it’s polite to call.

39:35.665 --> 39:38.623
You're joking!
You're mad at me?

39:38.877 --> 39:42.620
Sorry, but I’m not programmed
for that emotion at this time.

39:42.714 --> 39:44.045
(GRUNTING)

39:44.090 --> 39:45.876
I'm gonna kill Fargo!

39:53.975 --> 39:55.306
I'm sorry.

39:56.311 --> 39:58.176
It won't happen again.

40:00.523 --> 40:02.059
Now, I promise.

40:02.567 --> 40:04.228
(DOOR OPENING)

40:17.165 --> 40:19.827
SARAH, lights,

40:20.293 --> 40:21.908
fireplace, music.

40:22.754 --> 40:24.585
(MUSIC PLAYING)

40:41.814 --> 40:43.099
(SIGHING)

40:44.233 --> 40:46.485
SARAH:
If you’re hungry,
I can reheat dinner.

40:46.569 --> 40:48.105
Oh, no, just...

40:49.197 --> 40:51.688
You know,
if! could just
have a moment to myself.

40:54.911 --> 40:58.324
I've been dealing
with other people's
problems all day,

40:58.539 --> 41:02.031
and, you know,
I'd really like
a couple minutes of peace.

41:02.126 --> 41:04.117
All you had to do was ask.

41:04.295 --> 41:05.910
(MOTOR WHIRRING)

41:06.214 --> 41:07.203
Oh!

41:08.883 --> 41:10.293
(EXCLAIMING)

41:12.053 --> 41:13.133
Yeah.

41:16.391 --> 41:18.006
(BANGING ON DOOR)

41:19.477 --> 41:20.978
Just a minute.

41:22.647 --> 41:25.810
I swear, ifthis is
another Susan Perkins.

41:27.694 --> 41:29.650
Listen, I don't
mean to be rude...

41:29.737 --> 41:30.988
Hi, Dad!

41:32.281 --> 41:34.943
You know, your yard
needs a lot of work.

41:34.993 --> 41:37.780
Turns out it couldn't wait
till tomorrow.

41:37.912 --> 41:39.573
Have a good night.

